---
# Session Intel Configuration
# Copy to ~/.claude/session-intel.local.md and customize

# Number of days to look back by default (default: 1)
default_days: 1

# Include Codex sessions in analysis (default: true)
include_codex: true

# Filter to specific projects (empty = all projects)
projects: []

# Auto-save retro reports to file (default: true)
auto_save: true

# Retro report save path (default: ~/.claude/retro/)
save_path: ~/.claude/retro/

# Enable SessionEnd hook for auto-summaries (default: true)
auto_summary: true

# Session index location (default: ~/.claude/session-intel/index.json)
index_path: ~/.claude/session-intel/index.json

# Token pricing in USD per 1M tokens
pricing:
  claude-opus-4-6: { input: 15, output: 75, cache_read: 1.5 }
  claude-sonnet-4-6: { input: 3, output: 15, cache_read: 0.3 }
  claude-haiku-4-5: { input: 0.8, output: 4, cache_read: 0.1 }
  gpt-5.4: { input: 10, output: 30, cache_read: 1.0 }

# SessionDNA classification thresholds
dna_thresholds:
  explore: 3
  build: 2
  fix: 2
  chat: 0
---

# Session Intel Configuration

Copy this file to `~/.claude/session-intel.local.md` and customize the YAML values above.

Key settings:
- `default_days`: How far back /retro looks by default
- `projects`: Filter to specific projects (empty = all)
- `auto_summary`: Whether SessionEnd hook runs automatically
- `pricing`: Used by /cost-report for cost calculations
